It is difficult to suppress our scepticism in this new year, having gone through the toughest 10 months of our lives.On top of your usual resolutions, include the most important one: to keep the faith and remain optimistic. Over lunch with a friend on Wednesday, he jokingly pointed out that he will not be adding the year 2020 to his age because he hardly used it.
Similar jokes I have seen about 2020 include a hilarious one that some of us will not include 2020 in our CVs, and if quizzed about it by a hawk-eyed recruiter, we will tell them we spent 2020 washing hands, sanitising, maintaining social distance and wearing masks.



