That is what 2020 has been to all of us. A wasted year. A year of disappointments. Lost opportunities. Cancellations. Stolen dreams. Delayed achievements. A year of death and pain to nations and families.
It is difficult to suppress our scepticism in this new year, having gone through the toughest 10 months of our lives. However, my point — and the purpose of this column — is that there couldn’t be a better time to keep the faith and remain hopeful of the fact that 2021 will be a better year.



