I am writing to those of us who, at the beginning of last year, had plans for businesses, careers and lives but feel broken and cheated after a year of disappointments. 
I am writing to those who are feeling like failures for not achieving those dreams they had set. To those who, now looking at their 2020 resolutions, feel a lump in their throat and a sharp pain in their chest because they couldn’t have been further off the mark. 
Lost opportunities
To the students who expected to go to the next level but Covid stole the year from them. To the families who, together at the start of last year, made plans to complete —or start—their dream homes, to travel or do a family project but Covid stole that opportunity. 



