To those who lost businesses, jobs and opportunities. To the families who lost their loved ones this year, the most heart-wrenching pain a human being could ever experience, this is for you: That even when it is more practical to remain skeptical and pessimistic of 2021, we must never let go of those great ideas, plans and dreams we had for 2020.
To those who feel like failures for hardly getting anything done in 2020, the fact that you are still alive, that you can read this, is reason enough to be grateful and hopeful. That you are still breathing means there is still a lot fight left in you because there is no greater gift than the gift of life.
I know while many of us publicly denounce new year’s resolutions, deep down we list the things we must achieve at the beginning of the new year. Conventional resolutions have been to get fitter, read more, do better at work and school and get closer to God and family.
However, I encourage you to make an exception this new year. On top of your usual resolutions, include the most important one: to keep the faith and remain optimistic.
Dr Chege is the director of the Information Centre at the Aga Khan University; njokichegefeedback@gmail.com According to family members, the deceased was attached to the DP’s security detail for several years. The footbridge was damaged by a trailer carrying an excavator earlier in December 2020. However they made us feel, the men and women in this list elicited different emotions in all of us.